1
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,560
Impossible.

2
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,880
No, impossible.

3
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:20,719
Cheng Ye.

4
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,280
Where is your hearing aid?

5
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,760
I don't need it anymore.

6
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,640
How is that possible?

7
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,280
Impossible.

8
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:03,000
Hei Ba.

9
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,120
I want you dead.

10
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,920
I want you dead.

11
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:07,439
I'm going to kill you.

12
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:12,479
What a pity.

13
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,879
You won't get the chance to turn yourself in.

14
00:02:38,639 --> 00:02:40,319
I said no delivery guys allowed!

15
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:41,960
I'm here to play.

16
00:02:42,319 --> 00:02:44,159
Which crack did this country bumpkin crawl out of?

17
00:02:44,439 --> 00:02:45,680
Open your beady eyes and look closely.

18
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:46,520
This place...

19
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:48,159
is a high-end billiards club.

20
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:50,759
Not some roadside pit where you play street ball.

21
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,680
Hold on.

22
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:54,560
People like this...

23
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,560
touching them just makes you dirty.

24
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,599
Who knows what disease he has, trying to get back at society.

25
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:58,879
I'll give you three seconds.

26
00:02:58,919 --> 00:02:59,639
Get lost, now!

27
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:01,919
Found it.

28
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,000
He... he... he...

29
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,360
He actually has an invitation.

30
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,759
Welcome.

31
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,400
Hey, wait.

32
00:03:10,199 --> 00:03:10,759
What is this?

33
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,360
A handwritten signature?

34
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,840
In this club,

35
00:03:14,039 --> 00:03:15,879
even a mosquito needs to scan a chip to get in.

36
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,520
I knew it.

37
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:18,319
How could he have an invitation?

38
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:19,960
Turns out it's handwritten.

39
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,360
In terms of playing the fool,

40
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:23,080
isn't he quite the genius?

41
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,000
He certainly is.

42
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,800
You might not have the clearance.

43
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,240
Go ask your supervisor.

44
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,000
Ask my supervisor?

45
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,039
Go, go, go!

46
00:03:30,719 --> 00:03:31,960
You dare play us?

47
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,240
What are you doing?

48
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:38,879
Missy.

49
00:03:39,759 --> 00:03:41,039
What's wrong with delivery guys?

50
00:03:41,319 --> 00:03:43,280
Why can't a delivery guy be a player?

51
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,639
No profession is superior or inferior.

52
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:47,840
Nor should it be the standard for judging a person.

53
00:03:48,039 --> 00:03:49,719
And it's certainly no reason for you to discriminate against him.

54
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,439
Do I need to teach you how to verify it?

55
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:51,919
Missy.

56
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,000
We were wrong.

57
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,960
Why apologize to me?

58
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:56,800
Apologize to him.

59
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:57,360
Boss.

60
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,199
I was wrong.

61
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,479
We were blind to your greatness.

62
00:03:59,599 --> 00:04:00,680
We know we were wrong.

63
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,080
You...

64
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:04,639
from now on, just use your words.

65
00:04:04,919 --> 00:04:05,680
Don't get physical.

66
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,240
Yes, yes, yes.

67
00:04:06,759 --> 00:04:08,080
Careful, or the "country bumpkin" will take you out.

68
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,840
If you bully others again,

69
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:11,159
you're all fired!

70
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,560
Do you hear me?

71
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:14,039
We hear you, Missy.

72
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:18,879
Hei Ba.

73
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:22,000
Usually, I'm actually...

74
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,399
very gentle and delicate.

75
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,399
I... I know.

76
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,199
I know.

77
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:50,000
Dragon of the Middle Table.

78
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:50,959
The Violent Player.

79
00:04:50,959 --> 00:04:51,920
Iron Arm Hong.

80
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,800
It seems other than hitting the ball hard,

81
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,920
he doesn't have any other special traits.

82
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,800
This shot...

83
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,720
you won't make it.

84
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,079
It's not just about brute strength.

85
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,879
Then what did you see?

86
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,399
Handsome

87
00:05:48,519 --> 00:05:49,560
This shot of mine...

88
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,079
How was it?

89
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,959
Actually, you don't need to use this method

90
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,199
to distract me.

91
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:56,720
To be able to set up a layout like this,

92
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,720
you are already very impressive.

93
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,920
The honey trap won't work on me.

94
00:06:06,519 --> 00:06:07,560
Alright then.

95
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,879
Then let me see, Handsome,

96
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,519
just what you are capable of.

97
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,000
What's there to look at?

98
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,000
What are you doing?

99
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:21,000
You're here to play pool.

100
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,040
I know.

101
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:25,120
Is she one of the Five Dragons too?

102
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,360
Yes, yes, yes.

103
00:06:26,959 --> 00:06:28,759
The Nine-ball Dragon, Nine-Tailed Arc.

104
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:31,839
However,

105
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:33,600
according to my investigation,

106
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,519
she only knows how to play some

107
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:36,759
fancy spin shots.

108
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,480
I think

109
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:38,680
that Jiang Nan Shuo

110
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:39,759
just saw she has a nice figure

111
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:41,279
and brought her here as a gimmick.

112
00:06:41,959 --> 00:06:42,800
Look,

113
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,480
what is she wearing?

114
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,600
What about the other Five Dragons?

115
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:47,639
Hmm.

116
00:06:48,319 --> 00:06:48,839
Over there.

117
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,720
The Snooker Dragon,

118
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,040
Brother Wu Ba.

119
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,720
The match is over.

120
00:07:02,079 --> 00:07:03,120
Brother Wu Ba won.

121
00:07:03,319 --> 00:07:05,199
He still has so many balls left.

122
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,360
As expected.

123
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,160
As expected, every calculation of mine

124
00:07:22,319 --> 00:07:23,079
was correct.

125
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:25,079
Everyone has habits that are hard to break.

126
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:26,680
As long as the calculation is precise,

127
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:27,639
I can calculate

128
00:07:27,639 --> 00:07:28,759
the landing spot of your every shot.

129
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,519
You're calculating my shot path.

130
00:07:30,839 --> 00:07:31,240
Yes.

131
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:33,120
Although I can currently only calculate

132
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:34,240
your moves with 60% accuracy,

133
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,079
but

134
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,600
it's already enough to defeat you.

135
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:37,959
I'm a math genius, after all.

136
00:07:38,439 --> 00:07:39,560
Alright, math genius.

137
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,879
Show me

138
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:41,920
your math skills.

139
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,279
This Brother Wu Ba

140
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,680
is a math genius who's very popular online recently.

141
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,360
He excels at calculating opponents' shot paths.

142
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,720
He's very formidable.

143
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,480
He can be considered

144
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,560
among the so-called Five Dragons,

145
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,800
the strongest one.

146
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:56,560
Hei Ba,

147
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,439
you have to be careful.

148
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,000
I will.

149
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:03,040
I don't know if his algorithm

150
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,240
has improved much.

151
00:08:04,879 --> 00:08:05,519
You know him?

152
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:07,079
Not just him.

153
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,759
I've played against Iron Arm Hong

154
00:08:08,839 --> 00:08:10,040
and Nine-Tailed Arc before.

155
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,000
I know their strengths and weaknesses.

156
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,439
Then aren't you guaranteed to win?

157
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,399
But these are only three of the dragons.

158
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,639
What about the other two?

159
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,639
The other two,

160
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,360
I couldn't find them.

161
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:25,319
But they're also quite popular online recently.

162
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,120
They often design some

163
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:28,480
billiards puzzles.

164
00:08:28,879 --> 00:08:30,759
The account seems to be called

165
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,759
Xishi, Sister Wu and Ball Boy Wei He.

166
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:34,720
Known as

167
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,159
Puzzle Dragon.

168
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,919
No one knows their true identities.

169
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:40,879
Billiards puzzles

170
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:44,720
are about designing difficult Snooker scenarios,

171
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:47,600
like the Zhenlong puzzles in Go,

172
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,720
attracting everyone to try and solve them.

173
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:52,080
However, so far,

174
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,720
no one has been able to crack their layouts.

175
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:57,200
Sigh...

176
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:57,919
Don't worry.

177
00:08:58,559 --> 00:09:00,360
They never appear in person.

178
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,679
I guess

179
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:02,799
most likely

180
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:03,559
they are just

181
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,000
acting mysterious.

182
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:06,639
It doesn't matter.

183
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,279
We'll block soldiers with generals,

184
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,840
and stem floods with earth.

185
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,759
You are all extremely talented players.

186
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:29,399
I believe as long as we work together,

187
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,240
the title of the Eastern Five Dragons

188
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,000
will surely bring all of us

189
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,480
wealth and glory.

190
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:36,600
Didn't you say "Five Dragons"?

191
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,679
We're still missing two.

192
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,799
Yeah.

193
00:09:39,159 --> 00:09:40,840
They haven't shown their faces yet.

194
00:09:41,159 --> 00:09:42,600
Do they look down on us?

195
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:45,120
I wonder if they're even qualified

196
00:09:45,399 --> 00:09:47,000
to sit as equals with us.

197
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,120
Is their skill enough?

198
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:51,080
I can tell their playstyle at a glance.

199
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:52,240
The same goes for you two.

200
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,320
Alright.

201
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,600
Let's play a round.

202
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,000
Your playstyle is too simple.

203
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,759
It's boring.

204
00:09:57,759 --> 00:09:58,559
What did you say?

205
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,720
Hey, lady.

206
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,919
Who are you?

207
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,399
Didn't you want to see the other two?

208
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:09,360
This is

209
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:12,279
the viral online billiards puzzle master,

210
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:14,000
Xishi, Sister Wu.

211
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,919
Xishi, Sister Wu?

212
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,200
An auntie?
